  "body": "Usually, the service is the one that listens to status-go signals like this one, then it sends back a \"nim\" signal with the appropriate data if needed.\r\nThat's to create a separation of concerns I think. It's not a big deal, but I think it would be better to stay consistent.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @jrainville in https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/11061#discussion_r1228671603_\r\n            \r\n There's three controllers breaking the separation of concerns: [startup](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/fix/re-encrypt-db/src/app/modules/startup/controller.nim), [wallet activity](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/fix/re-encrypt-db/src/app/modules/main/wallet_section/activity/controller.nim#L209) and [node_section](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/fix/re-encrypt-db/src/app/modules/main/node_section/controller.nim#L43).",
